-- South Korea to Closely Monitor Currency Markets, Vice Minister Shin Says
-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 2011-12-19T22:47:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/south-korea-to-closely-monitor-currency-markets-vice-minister-shin-says.html
South Korean authorities will
closely monitor  currency markets  and the nation’s financial
markets have recovered fast from North Korea-related shocks in
the past, Vice Finance Minister Shin Je Yoon said at a meeting
with counterparts from the central bank and the financial
regulators.  Overseas investors’ attitude to the nation’s assets were
little changed after North Korean leader Kim Jong Il’s death
yesterday, Shin said today in  Seoul . The government will take
action to stabilize markets if needed, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eunkyung Seo in Seoul at 
